main event: A police officer observed a silvery, disc-shaped object hovering about 200 feet above the ground in Kettering, Ohio on June 30, 1966.
interesting points: The object was approximately 30 feet in diameter and made no sound.
The object remained motionless for about 5 minutes before accelerating rapidly and disappearing from view in a northerly direction.
The officer reported the sighting to his headquarters and stated that he had never witnessed anything like this before.
The Air Force requested additional data from the officer to further investigate the sighting.
The report includes a diagram showing the observer's position and the direction of the sighting.
